# Three-tier pricing architecture aligns price to value delivered across segments
@type: two_column

@col:
  ## Value-Based Price Setting
  - Segment customers by willingness-to-pay and value received
  - Build economic value models for each segment
  - Set list prices at 80–90% of full economic value
  - Annual price review tied to value delivery metrics
  - Target: 3–5% list price improvement in Year 1

@col:
  ## Discount Governance
  - Tiered discount authority: reps, managers, VP, C-suite
  - Real-time pricing guardrails in CRM/CPQ system
  - Compensation redesign: punish margin, reward volume + margin
  - Exception approval with documented value justification
  - Target: reduce unauthorized discounting by 60% in 12 months

@notes: The compensation redesign is the highest-leverage action. Sales reps optimize for what they are paid on — if discounting is rewarded implicitly through quota attainment, it will continue.

